article.description: — Cameron Tyson had 16 points and 13 rebounds in Seattle's 66-65 win against Utah Tech on Saturday night.
article.headline: Tyson's 16 points and 13 rebounds help Seattle knock off Utah Tech 66-65
article.linkText: Tyson's 16 points and 13 rebounds help Seattle knock off Utah Tech 66-65
article.story: ST. GEORGE, Utah -- — Cameron Tyson had 16 points and 13 rebounds in Seattle's 66-65 win against Utah Tech on Saturday night. Brandton Chatfield scored 13 points and added seven rebounds for the Redhawks (16-10, 9-6 Western Athletic Conference). Kobe Williamson went 5 of 9 from the field to finish with 12 points. Jaylen Searles finished with 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Trailblazers (10-16, 6-9). Aric Demings added 13 points for Utah Tech. In addition, Tanner Christensen and Noa Gonsalves scored 12 points apiece. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
